Title : Sonia Sotomayor Learning Academies
Text : '''Sonia M. Sotomayor Learning Academies''' is a complex of high schools and one middle school choice in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]. It is a part of the [[Los Angeles Unified School District]]. Sotomayor is made up of five individual schools.<ref>"[http://www.laschools.org/project-status/one-project?project_id=805892 Central Region HS #13, 56.40007]." [[Los Angeles Unified School District]]. Retrieved on April 27, 2014.</ref> The complex includes the Los Angeles River School (LARS), the School of History and Dramatic Arts (SoHDA), The studio school (middle school or junior high), Early College Academy of Leaders and Scholars (eCALS), and Tennenbaum Tech school (ATAMS).<ref name=Zonemap>"[https://web.archive.org/web/20140427050303/http://laschools.org/documents/download/mpd/school_year_2011-2012/school_year_2011-2012/Project02.pdf Proposed Changes to Sonia Sotomayor Learning Academies Area Schools, School Year 2011-2012]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6P8hlsD2n Archive]). [[Los Angeles Unified School District]]. Retrieved on April 27, 2014.</ref> It is named after [[Sonia Sotomayor]].

It opened in 2011, relieving [[Eagle Rock High School]], [[Franklin High School (Los Angeles)|Franklin High School]], [[Marshall High School (Los Angeles)|Marshall High School]], and the [[Belmont High School (Los Angeles)|Belmont High School]] Zone of Choice.<ref name=Zonemap/>

